OL,3,CPolice must separate offensive conduct
OL,4,Cfrom criminal, says watchdog
OL,6,FPolice should stop recording non-crime
OL,7,Fhate incidents and must "separate the
OL,8,Foffensive from the criminal", a
OL,9,Fwatchdog has said.
OL,11,FSir Andy Cooke, His Majesty's Chief
OL,12,FInspector of Constabulary, said
OL,13,Fofficers are placed in an invidious
OL,14,Fposition by current legislation and
OL,15,Fthat "discretion and common sense
OL,16,Fdon't always win out in these issues".
OL,18,FHe spoke to journalists ahead of the
OL,19,Fpublication of his organisation's
OL,20,Fannual report on the state of policing
OL,21,Fin England and Wales.
