OL,3,CPolice must separate offensive conduct
OL,4,Cfrom criminal, says watchdog
OL,6,F"The job of the police is to deal with
OL,7,Fcriminality across the board. That
OL,8,Fdoes mean dealing with some issues
OL,9,Fthat occur online and some of the
OL,10,Fthreats to life and other issues and
OL,11,Fthe serious issues that are there.
OL,13,F"It can be a fine line, and that's one
OL,14,Fof the reasons why we need to look
OL,15,Fagain at the policy and the
OL,16,Flegislation that sits around this
OL,17,Fbecause it places the police in an
OL,18,Finvidious position and, as we know,
OL,19,Fdiscretion and common sense don't
OL,20,Falways win out in these issues."
